As anticipation mounts ahead of the release of &#8220;Rogue One: A Star Wars Story,&#8221; Softbank is offering fans the chance to represent the dark side or the light side, via their phones.The Japanese brand is launching a pair of Star Wars Mobile Phones&#8217; with special light or dark covers, The Verge reports. The phones come with a host of Star Wars-themed functions, such as live wallpapers, special emoji and ringtones, and even a movie player app that means users can watch &#8220;The Force Awakens&#8221; on their handsets until 2020. The phones will be available from December 2 at http://www.softbank.jp/mobile/products/list/star-wars-mobile/. -Relaxnews